Here is the cleaned up text:

Set Up a Dialog Message Step

Use an Outbound Message step to send a message from the bot to your customer.

To add a Message step to the dialog, drag the Message step onto the canvas.
In the Step Properties panel, enter the outgoing message from your bot to the customer.

A message can be static text or dynamic text from merge fields. The merge field syntax is: {!API_VariableName} or {!API_VariableName.Field}.
To call a specific record, use {!Record.Field}.
To call an item in a list variable, use FieldName[X], with X referring to the location of the item in the list.
Einstein Bots uses a zero-based index with list variables.

Save the dialog.

Start the conversation between your bot and your customers with a friendly message that identifies the bot. For example, “Welcome! I’m Service Bot.”
title: Setting Up a Dialog Message Step in Service Cloud
